      <body>
         <div type="edition">
            <ab><supplied reason="lost">Ἱππό</supplied>δωρος Μενάνδρου χρηστέ χαῖρε</ab>
         </div>
         <div type="edition" subtype="secondary" n="beneath-female-in-arch">
            <ab>
               <gap reason="illegible" extent="unknown"/>ΩΙΣ
            </ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>farewell, worthy Hippodoros, son of Menander.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>the legible inscription commemorates the deceased, Hippodoros, who was probably the reclining figure.  
               the fragmentary inscription beneath the female figure is likely evidence that the stele was reused for another member of the family.</p>
         </div>
